ICE arrests man driving pregnant wife to hospital Immigration agents have arrested an undocumented immigrant who was driving his pregnant wife to hospital to give birth. Surveillance video shows Maria Del Cameran-Venegas, nine months pregnant, crying on the phone. Her husband, Joel Arrona-lara, was arrested by immigration officials at a petrol station in California while driving to the hospital for their child's birth. Cops wanted to see her ID and she took it out and gave it to them but her husband did not have his ID at the time. They arrested the husband saying he was illegally staying in the US. Maria had to drive herself to the hospital for her scheduled C-Section. 